18. How do you implement JWT Authentication?
=========================================================================
 -> JWT (JSON Web Token) is used for stateless authentication in Spring Boot APIs.
 -> After login, server gives a token ,Client sends that token in every request.
  Step 1: User Login
          POST /api/auth/login
  Step 2: Validate Credentials
          If valid → generate JWT token.
  Step 3: Return Token
			{
			  "token":"eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiJ9..."
			}
  Step 4: Client Sends Token in Every Request
			GET /api/employees
			Authorization: Bearer eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiJ9...
  Step 5: Filter Validates Token
  
  ✅ JWT Structure
       JWT has 3 parts: header.payload.signature
           
 19. How to pass token in API?
 =========================================================================
 -> To pass a token in an API, most commonly you send it in the HTTP Header using the Authorization header.
 
 20. How do you prevent unauthorized access?
 ===========================================================================
 -> We prevent unauthorized access by verifying user identity using authentication (login/JWT/OAuth),
    controlling permissions using authorization (roles), securing APIs with Spring Security, encrypting data, 
    validating tokens, and using HTTPS. 
    
 21. How to return large employee data efficiently?
 ===============================================================================
 -> For large employee data, I use pagination and sorting, fetch only required columns using DTO projections,
   optimize database queries with indexing. This improves performance and reduces memory usage.
   
