 23. How to improve slow API performance?
 ==========================================================================
 -> I improve slow API performance by profiling the API, optimizing database queries, adding pagination/caching,
    reducing unnecessary processing, using async operations where suitable, and monitoring response times.
  
 24. How to reduce DB calls?
 ========================================================================
 -> I reduce DB calls by using joins/fetch queries.
 -> Batching inserts/updates .
 -> caching frequently used data.
 -> avoiding repeated queries inside loops.
 -> selecting only required data in a single optimized query.
  
 25. What is caching in API?
 ========================================================================
 -> Caching is a mechanism it store frequently used data in temporarily, so that if those data required in 
    future it can serve the data without hitting the data base.
    
 26. Difference between save() and saveAndFlush() ?
 ========================================================================
 -> I use save() for normal inserts/updates because it is efficient and lets JPA manage flushing.
    I use saveAndFlush() only when I need immediate synchronization with the database
    
	| Feature                             | save()               | saveAndFlush()           |
	| ----------------------------------- | -------------------- | ------------------------ |
	| Persist entity                      | Yes                  | Yes                      |
	| Immediate DB write                  | No (usually delayed) | Yes                      |
	| Calls flush()                       | No                   | Yes                      |
	| Better performance for many records | Yes                  | No (more DB round trips) |
	| Use case                            | Standard save        | Need immediate sync      |
	
 27. What happens when invalid id passed?
 =============================================================================
 -> If an invalid ID is passed, I return 400 Bad Request. If the ID is valid but no record exists,
    I return 404 Not Found using proper exception handling.
    
 28. If same API hit by 1000 users, how handle?
 ============================================================================
  -> If 1000 users hit the same API, I ensure the application can scale horizontally, use efficient thread pools
     and connection pools, optimize database queries, add caching, and use load balancing so requests are distributed across multiple instances.
     
 29. If duplicate POST request comes, how prevent duplicate data?
 =============================================================================
  -> I prevent duplicate POST data using unique constraints at the database level,
     request idempotency keys, duplicate checks before insert
 -> Idempotency Key (Best for APIs)
    Client sends header:
                          Idempotency-Key: abc123
    If same key sent again:
        . Return previous response
        . Do not insert again
        
